Let us define a variable N that accepts integer inputs.
Output the same variable N.
To declare and integer variable, we use the int data type.

code:
#include <iostream>
#include <string>
using namespace std;

int main() 
{
int N;
 cin>>N;
 cout<<N;

}
6
6
######################################

Sometimes - we have to accept multiple inputs in a single line.
We can use the same syntax to accept multiple inputs in a single line, however the different inputs will be separated by a '>>' operator.

Now lets try and solve the following

Accept 3 space separated integers given in a line into 3 variables - 
A,B and C
Print them out to a single line on the console
You can play around with the exact syntax in the IDE -> refer to the solution in case you are unable to get this correct.
Code the solution in the IDE and then click Submit to continue.

code:
#include <iostream>
#include <string>
using namespace std;

int main() 
{
 int A,B,C;                                     //string A,B,C;     in case of strings       	(IMP)---->   's' --> s is small.
 cin>>A>>B>>C;
 cout<<A<<" "<<B<<" "<<C;
  return 0;
}

1 2 3
##########################################

#include <iostream>
#include <string>
using namespace std;

int main() 
{
int a = 5;
 cout<<a<<endl;
 		
 string b = "abcde";		
 cout<<b<<endl;
		
 int array[] = {1,2,3}; 
 cout<<array[0]<<" "<<array[1]<<" "<<array[2];	
}

5
abcde
1 2 3
